snippet.textDisplay: This song always makes me cry, I don't have a sister but this song and few other things made me realize that it's a very big thing for a girl to marry and leave the house where she was born, where she has all the memories and specially people with whom she used to live, laugh, cry, everything! Not just that but for the parents as well, they knew from the very first day she born that she will be marrying someone and will leave them but still LOVING HER MORE THAN ANYTHING, and when this day comes, maybe I can't feel their heart and emotions but I can understand what they must be going through! It's really important as a boy that we give her all she deserves, we should not make her feel that "kash woh uske ghar hoti" both should be her home, kabhi uski maarzi chal bhi jaaye, zidd kar bhi le, toh karne do, uske papa ne puri ki thi, kal tum papa banoge tum bhi karoge, fir uski zidd kyu nahi? I am sorry that only girls has to go through this and I don't have male ego or humiliation if i have to stay with her parents! We should normalize few important things <3 There will be fights, there are gonna be arguments, she did that with her parents as well but in the end, there needs a solution, there needs a peace, there needs a resolution which she always found at her home, again, don't let her feel like she is away from her home! It's easier for us to marry but it's difficult for her! Think about your mom what all love and care she deserves, maybe you will find more reasons to love your wife or future wife <3
